    "problemStatement": "You are given an array of **N** integers. You should support the following queries on this array.\n\n\n\n**0 L R** : Find the minimum integer in the range **AL, AL+1, ..., AR**.\n**1 L R X** :  You should apply the assignment **A[i] = A[i] &amp; X**, for all indices **i** in range **[L, R]**, where **&amp;** denotes bitwise AND operation.",
    "constraints": [
      "**1** ≤ **N, Q** ≤ **105**",
      "**1** ≤ **Ai**, **X** ≤ **109**",
      "**1** ≤ **L** ≤ **R** ≤ **N**",
      "Example**Input:**",
      "5 5",
      "1 5 2 3 4",
      "0 2 5",
      "1 1 5 6",
      "0 2 2",
      "1 2 5 3",
      "0 1 3",
      "**Output:**",
      "2",
      "4",
      "0"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "First line of the input contains two space separated integers **N** and **Q**.\n\nSecond line contains **N** integer numbers denoting array **A**.\n\nIn the next **Q** lines, each contain one of the queries described above.",
    "outputFormat": "For each query of the type **0**, output  a single line containing the answer of the query.",
